4. Evaluation Dataset Contains Personal Data. Upon NVIDIA's request, you will cooperate with NVIDIA to honor any data subject request for deletion or correction of the Evaluation Dataset. If requested by NVIDIA, you will delete all copies and cease use of any Evaluation Dataset and provide reasonably requested information to verify your compliance with the terms of this Agreement.

5. Distribution as Part of Academic Publication. Notwithstanding Section 2(c) above, you may distribute or reproduce a minimal, illustrative portion of the Evaluation Dataset solely as part of an academic publication (including a peer-reviewed journal article, conference paper, thesis, preprint, or research project website) that reports research results derived from your use of the Evaluation Dataset under this Agreement ("Academic Publication"), subject to all of the following conditions:
(a) Minimal Amount. The distributed or reproduced portion of the Evaluation Dataset must be limited to the minimum amount reasonably necessary to illustrate, support, or validate the specific findings reported in the Academic Publication (for example, representative still frames, short audio clips, or small tabular subsets used as figures or examples), and must not constitute a substantial or independently usable portion of the Evaluation Dataset.
(b) Non-Commercial Academic Context Only. The Academic Publication must be made available through a non-commercial academic or scientific channel (including open-access repositories, conference proceedings, or institutional repositories). The permission in this Section 5 does not extend to commercial publications, marketing materials, product documentation, or any other non-academic distribution.
(c) Attribution and Notice. Any reproduction or distribution of Evaluation Dataset content under this Section 5 must (i) include a clear and conspicuous attribution to NVIDIA and David AI as the source of the Evaluation Dataset and cite our paper [PLACEHOLDER TO BE UPDATED] in any published work; (ii) identify the content as being reproduced from the Evaluation Dataset under this Agreement; and (iii) include a statement that further use, reproduction, or distribution of the Evaluation Dataset requires a separate license from NVIDIA or its licensors.
(d) Compliance with Restrictions. All restrictions in Section 2(b) and Section 2(e) of this Agreement continue to apply to any portion of the Evaluation Dataset distributed or reproduced under this Section 5, including without limitation the prohibitions on identification of individuals, generation of likenesses, biometric processing, and use for any discriminatory or unlawful purpose.
This Section 5 does not permit redistribution of the Evaluation Dataset as a standalone dataset, as supplementary data files downloadable separately from the Academic Publication, or in any manner that would allow recipients to reconstruct a usable dataset from the distributed materials. Any distribution beyond the scope of this Section 5 requires NVIDIA's prior written consent.

